1using Moq;
2using System;
3using System.Collections.Generic;

10namespace Data.HashFunction.Test.Blake3
11{
12 public class Blake3_Implementation_Tests
13 {
14
15 #region Constructor
16
17 [Fact]
18 public void Blake3_Implementation_Constructor_ValidInputs_Works()
19 {
20 var hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock = new Mock<IBlake3Config>();
21 {
22 hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock.SetupGet(hawc => hawc.HashSizeInBits)
23 .Returns(64);
24
25 hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock.Setup(hawc => hawc.Clone())
26 .Returns(() => hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock.Object);
27 }
28
29
30 GC.KeepAlive(
31 new Blake3_Implementation(hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock.Object));
32 }
33
34 #region Config
35
36 [Fact]
37 public void Blake3_Implementation_Constructor_Config_IsNull_Throws()
38 {
39 Assert.Equal(
40 "config",
41 Assert.Throws<ArgumentNullException>(
42 () => new Blake3_Implementation(null))
43 .ParamName);
44 }
45
46 [Fact]
47 public void Blake3_Implementation_Constructor_Config_IsCloned()
48 {
49 var hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock = new Mock<IBlake3Config>();
50 {
51 hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock.Setup(hawc => hawc.Clone())
52 .Returns(
53 new Blake3Config());
54 }
55
56 GC.KeepAlive(
57 new Blake3_Implementation(hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock.Object));
58
59
60 hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock.Verify(fc => fc.Clone(), Times.Once);
61
62 hashAlgorithmWrapperConfigMock.VerifyGet(hawc => hawc.HashSizeInBits, Times.Never);
63 }
64
65 #endregion
66
67 #endregion
